extends baseChassisA

    Hex Motor Chassis

    Purpose:

    Contains the variables and functions specific to an all hex motor chassis

    so that we can switch from an all andymark motor chassis without changing any code!

        Hex Motor Chassis Specific encoderDrive()
        Parameters:
        driveFB - Inches to move forward or backward (forward: +, backward: -)
        turnDegrees - Degrees to turn left or right (right: +, left: -)
        speed - Speed of robot (min: 0, max: 1)
        turning - Whether robot is currently turning
        timerRequested - Whether this move is timed
        timerRequestTime - If move is timed, length of move is milliseconds
        opModeIsActive - Type "opModeIsActive()" boolean in autonomousFrame (program extending LinerOpMode)
        frame - Type "this" to pass in autonomousFrame (when calling in autonomousFrame) so this function can access it
